results.description:
♥ Our Personalized baby bracelet is simply adorable! It will make a great gift for baby shower, baby's birthdays, Baptism, etc.  The length is suggested according to age average. We make it adjustable if you are not sure about baby's wrist size and for perspective baby's growth ♥

M A T E R I A L S · A N D · D E T A I L S

*** We use the highest quality USA and Italy made materials:
     - 925 Sterling silver,
     - 14K Gold filled
     - Rose gold filled 
*** Bar size - 30x5mm (approx. 1.25"x3/16”)
*** Bar thickness - 1mm;
*** Chain - sturdy and durable 2.0 mm rollo chain.
*** Available with or without CZ charm


H O W · T O · O R D E R

*** Select your bracelet's Color (Silver, Gold or Rose Gold), 1 or 2 sided engraving, and the option With or Without birthstone 
      (STONE) from the first drop down menu;
NOTE: for this item we use Swarovski Cubic Zirconia charms instead of the gemstones because of the stronger 
            interlocking connection, so that the kids would NOT BE ABLE to brake them
*** Select bracelet`s length from the second drop down menu; 
*** If you need custom length, we can make it, just let us know;
*** Scroll through the pictures and find the FONTS & SYMBOLS chart. We offer 17 fonts and many symbols
       NOTE: Default font is #6 - Kiddo


P E R S O N A L I Z A T I O N

*** Write your personalization in the Personalization box. Please, make your request short and clear. 
      Hardly understandable personalization will significantly slow down completion process.
*** Write your engraving EXACTLY AS YOU WANT IT TO APPEAR. For example, if you indicated that you want name Emily, we will engrave E uppercase and rest of the letters lowercase. If you indicate that you want SARAH, we will engrave SARAH in all uppercase. 


M A X I M U M ∙ C H A R A C T E R S 

*** The maximum characters we can fit on the bar are 12-15, including spaces, depending of the chosen font. If you need slightly more characters, please be aware that the text will be smaller.



A L I G N M E N T

*** If you have a preference, choose your ALIGNMENT. By default, the engraving for baby's bracelet is  CENTERED.


F I N I S H

*** We can make characters PLAIN or BLACKENED. Default finish is PLAIN.


P A C K A G I N G 

*** All of our jewelry arrives packaged in nice boxes with a cute surprise inside it. It's ready to be presented as a gift.
*** If you want a personalized message sent with the order to your recipient, the option is available.


P R O D U C T I O N ∙ T I M E

*** All of our items are made to order. Please check our shop policies for the most up-to-date information. If you need your order expedited, please let us know directly through our Etsy shop. Most of the time we are able rush your order with no extra charge and ensure prompt shipping. 


H O W ∙ T O ∙ D E T E R M I N E ∙ Y O U R ∙ B R A C E L E T’ S ∙ S I Z E?

*** Measure baby's wrist with a string or paper strip and put it against the ruler. Add 1/2" for normal fit. Other option - choose the length using our age average measurements.
I M P O R T A N T : Please note that BARS and TEXT in the pictures usually look BIGGER than in person. It is best to read all 
      items' dimensions before ordering and compare them to the ruler.


W H A T ∙ I S ∙ G O L D ∙ F I L L E D ∙ J E W E L R Y ?

*** Gold filled is an actual layer of pure Gold pressure bonded to another metal. Gold filled is not to be confused with gold plated as Gold filled literally has 100% more gold than gold plated. 
*** With proper care, Gold filled pieces can last 10- 15 years. Gold filled contains 100 (+) times more pure gold as gold plated - it has real gold beauty but it's a lot more affordable. 
*** One of the most important things about Gold filled- it's absolutely tarnish resistant. It does not flake off, rub off or turn 
      colors. It will usually maintain its golden shine for a very long time if it's not exposed to harsh chemicals.
*** Anyone who can wear real gold can wear Gold filled without the worry of any allergic reaction. 
*** Gold filled is constructed in several layers. The core metal is jewelers’ brass. A gold alloy is then bonded to one or both surfaces of the brass core with heat legally required to contain 5% or 1/20 gold by weight. This 5% is then described by the Karats of the gold alloy. We use 14K Gold-filled and Rose Gold-filled items.

H O W ∙ T O ∙ T A K E ∙ C A R E ∙ O F ∙ G O L D ∙ F I L L E D ∙ J E W E L R Y ?

*** As a common rule, all jewelry should be cleaned on a regular basis, but Gold Filled jewelry is much more prone to damage from environmental impact as does Silver jewelry. However, we recommend avoid direct contact with chemicals, such as aggressive perfumes, creams or any other harsh liquids. We recommend removing your jewelry when you engage in heavy exercise or swimming, or bathing, especially if you have a bracelet with a gemstone. Some gemstones are very sensitive to moisture since they can absorb water. All of these threats may result in change of color and flash of your jewelry over time.
*** Many Gold-filled jewelry owners find that they never have to clean gold-filled items at all. We recommend clean it from time to time because it simply may become dirty from everyday wear. Wash your Gold Filled and Rose Gold Filled jewelry with mildly soapy water and clean with a soft cloth, That's it! 

W H A T ∙ Y O U ∙ S H O U L D ∙ K N O W ∙ A B O U T ∙ S T E R L I N G ∙ S I L V E R ?

*** All Sterling silver will tarnish over time when it is exposed to air and light. Silver tarnishes faster in areas with high humidity and air pollution. Chemicals like hairspray, perfume, body lotion, deodorant, bleach, also food products high in sulfur, such as eggs and onions, or acids, such as vinegar, olives and fruit juice will speed tarnishing process.

*** Body chemistry is another big culprit for silver tarnishing. Changes in body chemistry can affect the tarnish rate 
      significantly. Amino acids in the perspiration contain sulfur or sulfides and the presence of sulfur or sulfides accelerates the rate of tarnish. Changes in hormone balance during adolescence or change of life in women has been known to change the body’s chemistry. Medications, including vitamins, chemotherapy can also effect the body chemistry. Sometimes chemicals during sweating could have so harsh ingredients that your silver jewelry could tarnish simply overnight.

      Thus, we do not recommend wearing silver jewelry while taking bath, swimming in the sea or pool, taking hot tub and when you engage in heavy exercise. If the sterling silver tarnishes simply from wearing it, think about your body chemistry.

H O W ∙ T O ∙ T A K E ∙ C A R E ∙ O F ∙ S T E R L I N G ∙ S I L V E R ∙ J E W E L R Y ?

     Because of its composition, silver needs more attention and care than other metals. The good news is that it is easy to 
     clean. There are many ways to make your sterling silver shine.

   - Washing and cleaning with soft cloth 
       Make sure you wash the item off in soapy (with mild detergent) water and then run it under clean water. Rub it with a 100- percent cotton or flannel cloth to get rid of water stains. 


    - Cleaning with baking soda or toothpaste. 
       Baking soda or toothpaste with baking soda are another common household items that you can use to clean sterling silver. 
       Coat the item with baking soda or toothpaste and rub it with a soft cloth. Rinse it under warm water and dry. If you decide to use a toothbrush, make sure it is one with extra-soft bristles.


     - Cleaning with precious metal cleaner and soft cloth
       Polish your sterling silver jewelry with a soft cloth and precious metal cleaner such as Blitz Silvershine. Be gentle! Harsh polishing and aggressive buffing can permanently damage and devalue a piece of silver.


     - Cleaning with special polish cloth or liquid silver cleaners
        Industry makes a simple polish cloth with polish ingredients already in it. It's called a Sunshine Cloth and it’s great for shining up silver - it removes tarnish surprisingly quickly and easily. Also, there are silver liquid cleaners (I use “Hagerty silver clean”) for silver cleaning. Simply soak your silver jewelry in it for couple minutes and wash it with clean water.
    Note of caution: Don’t use this method if you jewelry has a gemstones: liquid will destroy them.


      - Cleaning with homemade electrochemical solution.
        You can shine your sterling silver with some basic kitchen supplies. Line the bottom of your glass dish with aluminum foil. 
        Place your sterling silver inside. Pour a cup of boiling water along with two tablespoons of baking soda and one teaspoon of salt. After a few minutes the tarnish will jump from the jewelry to the foil! (Note: Leave heavily tarnished items in the solution for up to 5 minutes). Rinse the silver with water and dry it right away to avoid water spots.
    Note of caution: Do not use this method if your jewelry has pearls or gemstones.


H O W ∙ T O ∙ S T O R E ∙ S T E R L I N G ∙ S I L V E R ∙ J E W E L R Y ?

       - Storage is a very important component of sterling silver care.
         Keep the jewelry clean and dry when you’re not wearing it. Place it in air-tight bags or containers to protect it from 
         moisture and chemicals that can be in the air. Place it in an anti-tarnishing bag. There are lots of anti-tarnishing bags 
         on the market that can be used to protect silver jewelry from tarnishing. Store silver separately from other metals.


*** For more items please enter our shop here:
         https://www.etsy.com/shop/JewelryBlues?ref=si_shop

        Thank you for stopping by!

results.description:
Colon cleansing tea can help improve your body’s overall health and wellness. 


1. Helps make the digestive system more efficient 

As the colon is cleansed, it pushes waste through your system, clearing the way for good nutrient absorption. A clean colon from a colon detox allows waste to pass easily.

2. Maintains regularly and prevents constipation. 

Constipation — especially when it's chronic — causes a sluggish digestive response, which in turn leaves waste in the system longer. This increases the likelihood of certain conditions and irritations, such as hemorrhoids and varicose veins.

3. Increase energy

Releasing the toxins from your body is rejuvenating because it refocuses the energy usually used for forcing waste through your intestines to other parts of your body. People who have undergone colon detoxification say they have better blood circulation, more restful sleep, and a boost in energy.


4. Increase the bodies absorption to nutrients and vitamins

A colon that's been cleansed allows only water, vitamins and nutrients to be absorbed into the bloodstream, creating an unobstructed path for essential nutrients to filter into your body.

5. Improves concentration

Poor diet and ineffective vitamin absorption can cause you to become distracted and lose your concentration. The buildup of mucous and toxins in your colon can keep your body from getting what it needs to function, even if you eat a consistently healthy diet. Cleansing the colon with a detox diet can be the difference between feeling alert and not being able to focus. This has far-reaching ramifications for work, your relationships, and your overall health.

6. Kickstart weight loss

Foods lacking in fiber move through the digestive tract at one-quarter the pace of high-fiber choices. This slow-moving food produces excess mucous that literally sticks to the intestinal walls, weighing the intestinal tract down with pounds of decaying fecal matter. Colon cleansing has the potential to aid weight loss; some people claim to have lost up to 20 pounds over the course of a month. The average human colon weighs about four pounds empty and can hold up to eight meals' worth of food before digestion finally occurs. A colon cleansing can result in significant weight loss and kick-start your metabolism, as well as refocus your attention on better food choices and whole-body wellness.
